<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-343-256  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 343 256.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  June 12 1989 v8 n12 p142(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>TRW group wins Air Force award. (TRW Defense Systems Group)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   TRW Defense Systems Group (achievements and awards).andO;Topic:     Achievements and AwardsUnited States. Air ForceGovernment ContractsNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>TRW Group Wins Air Force AwardandM;TRW Defense Systems Group of Carson, Calif., has won the first TrustedContractor Award given by the Air Force Electronic Systems Division's AirBase Decisions Systems.andM;Working under a contract awarded by the Air Force in 1985, TRW has installedbroadband local area networks at five of the service's Air Logistics Centers.andM;Julie Meier Wright, a TRW spokeswoman, said the Defense System Group wascited for work that included installation in 1987 of the largest broadbandnetwork in the free world at Hill Air Force Base in Ogden, Utah.andM;Wright said exercised options have brought the contract value to more than$100 million.andM;Each of the five sites has been developed for computerized communications,she said, and all work should be completed by late this year.andO;</TEXT></DOC>